parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake calipers can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Rear brakes do not stop the vehicle while on rollers
rear brakes do not stop the wheels when the vehicle is raised and in drive
parking brake sticks
and the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Accelerator goes to the floor without foot on pedal
vehicle lurches forward with brakes applied
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can compromise the safety of the driver and passengers in the event of a collision, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is broken
the seat belt will not retract
the seat belt is unable to be used
the seat belt fails to protect the driver or passenger in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure leading to No-Start Condition and Fire Hazards
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to not start, and in extreme cases, lead to fires, posing a significant risk to the safety of the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The security light comes on and stays on
the vehicle won't start
the starter fails to engage
the ignition cylinder and switch fail
the battery drains frequently
the vehicle catches fire
especially in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the vehicle can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially at low speeds. This can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently while traveling at low speeds (10-30mph)
causing the steering and brakes to lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusted fuel line clamps can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from both connections due to rusted clamps that secure the fuel lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Fire after Fuel Line Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle fire can cause serious injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: Vehicle fire after recall repair on fuel line (90V115).
